<h3>Customize your BYU-Idaho University Studies Degree</h3>
<p>A University Studies degree offers students a flexible option for graduating with a Bachelor's of Science degree. &nbsp;The requirements for the University Studies degree are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Completion of foundations courses</li>
<li>Completion of <a href="http://www.byui.edu/academic-discovery-center/students/academic-advising-and-class-planning/general-academic-requirements/university-requirements">university requirements</a> (see university catalog)</li>
<li>A minor and two clusters or two minors and one cluster</li>
<li>15 credits must be upper division from BYU-Idaho (online or on campus)</li>
<li>30 credits must be taken online through BYU-Idaho</li>
</ul>
<h3>What are the Classes Like?</h3>
<p>BYU-Idaho's online courses mirror campus courses. Classes follow the same semester format and use the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/learningmodel/src/default.htm">learning model</a>. Students will have regular due dates for assignments and should expect to interact with their instructors and peers often.</p>
<h3>How Long will this Program Take?</h3>
<p>Our online degree program allows students the flexibility to finish their degree while balancing a busy life. Students can accelerate to graduation by taking classes all three semesters each year, or take a semester off when needed. Students must complete the program within eight years.</p>
<h3>What will I Study?</h3>
<p>Students may choose either two minors and one cluster, or two clusters and one minor.</p>
